1
00:00:36,110 --> 00:00:41,240
♪In rain or shine♪

2
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:46,870
♪When you're around,
the sun shines through♪

3
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Spare ourselves the endless thoughts
and guessing games♪

4
00:00:52,930 --> 00:00:58,880
♪Let's just meet
and escape these frames♪

5
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:02,600
♪I stand within the shadows deep♪

6
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:08,030
♪My hand outstretched,
your rescue I keep♪

7
00:01:08,220 --> 00:01:12,850
♪Even if the world falls apart♪

8
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:15,870
♪No distance is too far♪

9
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:21,390
♪To stop us from coming together♪

10
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:27,710
♪Through the night,
you're at the end of the line♪

11
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:32,730
♪To protect you is my humble wish♪

12
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:36,920
♪Farewell, to the timid soul I knew♪

13
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:42,550
♪It was you who made me brave and new♪

14
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:46,180
=Always Home=
(Adapted from Xiao Ge's novel, Always Home)

15
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:49,180
=Episode 25=
(This Is The Real Me)

16
00:01:57,630 --> 00:01:58,580
Hello, what's up?

17
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,030
I'm at the door.

18
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:01,300
Now?

19
00:02:02,110 --> 00:02:03,110
I... Wait a minute.

20
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:11,600
Good morning.

21
00:02:12,390 --> 00:02:12,900
You're here.

22
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:14,620
Am I too early?

23
00:02:16,230 --> 00:02:17,070
A little.

24
00:02:18,020 --> 00:02:18,900
Come in first.

25
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:19,830
Keep it down.

26
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:20,300
Okay.

27
00:02:33,622 --> 00:02:35,070
What's wrong with your back?

28
00:02:37,020 --> 00:02:37,420
Nothing.

29
00:02:37,460 --> 00:02:38,790
I kind of sprained it

30
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:39,830
yesterday.

31
00:02:40,510 --> 00:02:41,790
Well, sit down now.

32
00:02:42,133 --> 00:02:43,510
I haven't finished packing yet.

33
00:02:43,510 --> 00:02:44,488
I'll be done in a minute.

34
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:46,950
So where do I sit?

35
00:02:47,510 --> 00:02:49,070
Wherever you like.

36
00:02:50,510 --> 00:02:51,580
Just like old times.

37
00:02:52,070 --> 00:02:53,830
How can it be the same?

38
00:02:54,230 --> 00:02:56,070
My status is different now,

39
00:02:56,620 --> 00:02:58,790
so my mindset must be different too.

40
00:03:04,550 --> 00:03:05,155
Huan'er,

41
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:07,790
when are we going

42
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:09,550
to tell the parents about us?

43
00:03:11,110 --> 00:03:11,460
I...

44
00:03:12,070 --> 00:03:12,550
Huan'er.

45
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:13,510
Huan'er.

46
00:03:13,830 --> 00:03:14,300
Uncle Chen.

47
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:16,460
Xichi is here.

48
00:03:18,230 --> 00:03:19,070
No, it's so early.

49
00:03:19,110 --> 00:03:20,350
What are you two doing here?

50
00:03:22,555 --> 00:03:24,300
Well, school's about to start, isn't it?

51
00:03:24,620 --> 00:03:26,420
I'm discussing something with Huan'er.

52
00:03:26,860 --> 00:03:27,180
Yes.

53
00:03:27,550 --> 00:03:27,830
Dad,

54
00:03:28,070 --> 00:03:28,740
where is Mom?

55
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:29,844
She's still sleeping.

56
00:03:29,844 --> 00:03:30,333
Right,

57
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:31,270
bring more clothes

58
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:32,390
this time.

59
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:33,740
Separate the toiletries

60
00:03:33,740 --> 00:03:34,790
from the clothes.

61
00:03:34,830 --> 00:03:36,977
Don't get it all over the place
like last time.

62
00:03:36,977 --> 00:03:37,400
Okay.

63
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,990
I've packed them all.

64
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,110
You packed well this time.

65
00:03:44,110 --> 00:03:45,510
My Huan'er has grown up.

66
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:47,700
Xichi,

67
00:03:48,044 --> 00:03:49,900
it's been hard on you
these past few days.

68
00:03:49,990 --> 00:03:50,460
No.

69
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:51,490
This is what I should do.

70
00:03:52,350 --> 00:03:54,700
There's something else
I'd like to ask you.

71
00:03:55,070 --> 00:03:55,700
Go ahead, Uncle.

72
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:56,790
That is,

73
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:58,070
when you go to school,

74
00:03:58,270 --> 00:04:00,460
take care of Huan'er for me.

75
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:01,790
No problem.

76
00:04:01,830 --> 00:04:02,950
I know

77
00:04:02,990 --> 00:04:04,070
there are many

78
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:05,230
handsome guys

79
00:04:05,270 --> 00:04:06,020
and temptations

80
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:07,140
in the university.

81
00:04:08,110 --> 00:04:09,790
Keep a close eye on her.

82
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:11,110
Don't let any boys

83
00:04:11,110 --> 00:04:12,420
trick my girl away.

84
00:04:12,550 --> 00:04:13,390
Dad,

85
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:15,420
what are you saying?

86
00:04:15,620 --> 00:04:16,620
You tell me.

87
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,000
- Okay?
- Sure.

88
00:04:18,088 --> 00:04:18,790
No problem, Uncle.

89
00:04:18,790 --> 00:04:19,420
Don't worry.

90
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:20,888
I will take good care of Huan'er.

91
00:04:20,888 --> 00:04:21,511
Good.

92
00:04:21,790 --> 00:04:22,420
I will

93
00:04:22,940 --> 00:04:24,150
leave her to you then.

94
00:04:25,955 --> 00:04:27,420
I'll make you two some breakfast.

95
00:04:27,666 --> 00:04:28,933
You two can have a chat.

96
00:04:29,180 --> 00:04:29,500
Okay.

97
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:39,300
No.

98
00:04:39,380 --> 00:04:39,860
Now, I...

99
00:04:40,260 --> 00:04:40,790
Seriously.

100
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:41,860
With your dad saying that,

101
00:04:41,940 --> 00:04:42,910
I feel like

102
00:04:42,910 --> 00:04:44,822
the big bad wolf
that steals what it guards.

103
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:45,820
What to do?

104
00:04:47,860 --> 00:04:49,500
Then why don't we keep it

105
00:04:49,740 --> 00:04:50,710
from our family first,

106
00:04:50,710 --> 00:04:51,622
especially my dad?

107
00:04:51,710 --> 00:04:52,740
He's probably

108
00:04:52,740 --> 00:04:53,620
not ready

109
00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:55,180
to accept our relationship right now.

110
00:04:58,180 --> 00:04:58,620
Okay.

111
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,088
By the way,

112
00:05:01,777 --> 00:05:02,755
you haven't told

113
00:05:02,888 --> 00:05:04,800
Qi Qi and Song Cong about us, have you?

114
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:06,180
I...

115
00:05:06,230 --> 00:05:07,150
They already know.

116
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:08,150
When?

117
00:05:08,380 --> 00:05:09,350
I told them last night.

118
00:05:10,030 --> 00:05:11,110
Why didn't you tell me?

119
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:12,060
My back hurts.

120
00:05:12,380 --> 00:05:12,990
Xichi,

121
00:05:13,110 --> 00:05:14,620
do you eat milk and eggs?

122
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:17,790
I'm not eating, Uncle.

123
00:05:17,790 --> 00:05:18,777
I have something to do.

124
00:05:18,822 --> 00:05:19,900
I'll go now.
I'm not eating.

125
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:20,710
Have breakfast here.

126
00:05:20,710 --> 00:05:21,822
How dare I sit here and eat?

127
00:05:22,710 --> 00:05:23,500
Bye, Uncle.

128
00:05:28,030 --> 00:05:28,350
Thanks.

129
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:33,400
Be careful. It's hot.

130
00:05:37,620 --> 00:05:38,180
Thank you.

131
00:05:40,622 --> 00:05:41,466
It's so good.

132
00:05:45,244 --> 00:05:46,600
You've got it on your lips.

133
00:05:46,622 --> 00:05:47,111
Wipe it.

134
00:05:47,710 --> 00:05:48,620
Stop it.

135
00:05:48,620 --> 00:05:49,820
They're sitting here watching.

136
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:51,110
What's wrong?

137
00:05:52,230 --> 00:05:53,355
I'll wipe it myself.

138
00:05:53,533 --> 00:05:54,550
They're watching us.

139
00:05:54,550 --> 00:05:55,420
What's wrong?

140
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:57,230
They're calm.

141
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:58,740
They don't feel anything

142
00:05:58,755 --> 00:05:59,844
and they're not surprised.

143
00:05:59,910 --> 00:06:00,910
We knew you two

144
00:06:00,910 --> 00:06:01,620
would be together.

145
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:03,380
The whole world knew

146
00:06:03,380 --> 00:06:04,511
you liked each other.

147
00:06:05,110 --> 00:06:06,230
Is it that obvious?

148
00:06:07,030 --> 00:06:08,110
Is it not?

149
00:06:08,150 --> 00:06:09,777
You've been hanging around her all day.

150
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:11,710
Huan'er,

151
00:06:12,350 --> 00:06:12,940
listen.

152
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:15,300
Jing has liked you for a long time.

153
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,150
He was afraid
to confess his love to you.

154
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:18,444
He feared you'd reject him.

155
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,577
Really?

156
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,300
Since when?

157
00:06:22,030 --> 00:06:23,790
About since...

158
00:06:23,790 --> 00:06:24,230
Song Cong,

159
00:06:25,710 --> 00:06:26,420
can you stop

160
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:27,150
telling everything

161
00:06:27,150 --> 00:06:28,350
like a bullhorn?

162
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:29,710
Okay.

163
00:06:31,311 --> 00:06:32,355
Since high school?

164
00:06:32,790 --> 00:06:33,110
No.

165
00:06:33,155 --> 00:06:33,710
Not so early.

166
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:34,380
Since high school?

167
00:06:34,380 --> 00:06:35,820
Last Thursday night,

168
00:06:36,030 --> 00:06:37,110
around 8:40 PM.

169
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:40,060
We're still here.

170
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:41,400
Stop displaying affection.

171
00:06:41,710 --> 00:06:43,300
Are you going back to school tomorrow?

172
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:45,150
Yes.

173
00:06:45,911 --> 00:06:46,733
What about you?

174
00:06:46,933 --> 00:06:48,200
We're going back tomorrow too.

175
00:06:49,022 --> 00:06:50,150
I've got to leave quickly.

176
00:06:50,260 --> 00:06:51,470
After I changed my major,

177
00:06:51,488 --> 00:06:53,400
my mom has been impatient
with me every day.

178
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:54,200
I can't stand it.

179
00:06:55,377 --> 00:06:57,133
Did you get the connecting tickets?

180
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,620
Tickets are hard to come by now.

181
00:06:59,030 --> 00:07:00,590
We'll have to sit separately.

182
00:07:01,590 --> 00:07:02,230
No.

183
00:07:03,710 --> 00:07:04,420
Song Cong,

184
00:07:04,888 --> 00:07:06,466
which compartment did you get?

185
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:07,740
Let me see.

186
00:07:12,030 --> 00:07:12,733
Twelve.

187
00:07:12,955 --> 00:07:13,590
What about you?

188
00:07:13,590 --> 00:07:14,260
Twelve?

189
00:07:14,688 --> 00:07:16,066
You bought a second-class seat?

190
00:07:16,088 --> 00:07:16,622
Yes.

191
00:07:18,488 --> 00:07:19,111
It's okay.

192
00:07:19,330 --> 00:07:20,320
I'm sure they'd be willing

193
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,600
to exchange a business class seat

194
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,590
for a second-class seat.

195
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:23,740
I want to sit with you.

196
00:07:24,940 --> 00:07:25,620
Don't do that.

197
00:07:26,620 --> 00:07:28,350
We're just not on the road together.

198
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,990
When we get to Jing City,
I'll take you back to school.

199
00:07:31,066 --> 00:07:31,740
It's okay.

200
00:07:31,740 --> 00:07:33,030
It isn't worth much.

201
00:07:33,790 --> 00:07:34,470
It's decided.

202
00:07:43,710 --> 00:07:44,150
Qi Qi,

203
00:07:44,844 --> 00:07:45,800
didn't your mom

204
00:07:45,820 --> 00:07:47,060
stop your card

205
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:48,355
because you changed your major?

206
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:50,500
I sold some of my old clothes

207
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,110
and bags.

208
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:52,088
So it's still okay.

209
00:08:20,590 --> 00:08:22,030
I read the novel

210
00:08:22,244 --> 00:08:23,466
you posted online.

211
00:08:23,888 --> 00:08:25,533
What are you trying to satirize?

212
00:08:27,260 --> 00:08:28,820
The wording is a bit childish

213
00:08:29,790 --> 00:08:31,150
and the idea a bit cliched,

214
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:32,860
but I admit

215
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:35,710
that you have perception and talent.

216
00:08:40,310 --> 00:08:41,900
If you really want to study literature,

217
00:08:43,070 --> 00:08:44,380
I think you should go abroad.

218
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,830
Aunt Zhou's daughter

219
00:08:46,830 --> 00:08:48,200
is studying literature at Cambridge.

220
00:08:48,244 --> 00:08:49,444
You can contact her.

221
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:51,620
I don't want to go abroad.

222
00:08:52,780 --> 00:08:55,070
You don't just need talent
to study literature,

223
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:57,430
and you need vision, insight,

224
00:08:57,430 --> 00:08:59,244
experience
and a philosophical foundation.

225
00:08:59,355 --> 00:09:00,666
No matter what direction

226
00:09:00,666 --> 00:09:02,355
you're going to take in the future,

227
00:09:02,377 --> 00:09:03,866
the experience of studying abroad

228
00:09:03,866 --> 00:09:05,990
will definitely nourish your creativity.

229
00:09:07,430 --> 00:09:08,950
But writing for a living

230
00:09:09,430 --> 00:09:10,830
on a second-rate website

231
00:09:11,350 --> 00:09:12,140
only saps

232
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:13,260
your passion for literature.

233
00:09:18,466 --> 00:09:19,977
Are you afraid your boyfriend

234
00:09:21,020 --> 00:09:22,500
will stop you from going abroad?

235
00:09:25,860 --> 00:09:26,830
Listen here.

236
00:09:27,470 --> 00:09:28,830
Only incompetent men

237
00:09:29,190 --> 00:09:29,860
hold back

238
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,190
the progress of their partners.

239
00:09:36,830 --> 00:09:37,830
Think about it.

240
00:09:41,990 --> 00:09:43,780
Since you're going after your dreams,

241
00:09:45,190 --> 00:09:46,590
I want you to have no regrets.

242
00:10:05,310 --> 00:10:06,110
Are you tired?

243
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:06,590
No.

244
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:07,900
This is nothing.

245
00:10:07,955 --> 00:10:09,444
Have you forgotten that I have muscles?

246
00:10:09,444 --> 00:10:10,710
I'm strong.

247
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:11,540
Enough.

248
00:10:11,620 --> 00:10:12,066
Alright.

249
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:16,644
I've arrived.

250
00:10:16,755 --> 00:10:17,466
Give it to me.

251
00:10:18,020 --> 00:10:18,710
I'll walk you up.

252
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:19,950
I'll go up myself.

253
00:10:20,488 --> 00:10:21,400
By the way,

254
00:10:21,780 --> 00:10:22,780
should we tell

255
00:10:23,430 --> 00:10:23,830
Zhou Ye

256
00:10:23,830 --> 00:10:25,511
and the others about us?

257
00:10:26,830 --> 00:10:27,110
Okay.

258
00:10:27,244 --> 00:10:28,620
I'll go back and find a chance

259
00:10:28,620 --> 00:10:29,355
to tell them.

260
00:10:30,430 --> 00:10:30,710
Okay.

261
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:31,350
Xichi,

262
00:10:32,266 --> 00:10:33,066
Huan'er.

263
00:10:33,230 --> 00:10:33,950
Huixin.

264
00:10:34,022 --> 00:10:35,260
It's good that you're all back.

265
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:36,230
Call your roommates

266
00:10:36,266 --> 00:10:37,880
and have dinner
in our dormitory tonight.

267
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:39,800
I've brought a lot of specialties
back from home.

268
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:40,977
We'll make a hot pot together.

269
00:10:41,430 --> 00:10:43,310
Isn't it inconvenient for us girls

270
00:10:43,310 --> 00:10:44,540
to go to the boys' dormitory?

271
00:10:44,860 --> 00:10:45,830
Not really.

272
00:10:46,110 --> 00:10:47,800
Our dormitory isn't as strict as yours.

273
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,130
Besides, it gets crowded at night.

274
00:10:49,130 --> 00:10:50,709
Then we boys will cover them together,

275
00:10:50,710 --> 00:10:51,688
and they'll sneak in.

276
00:10:53,470 --> 00:10:54,500
Come on, Huan'er.

277
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:55,620
Or Huixin will be alone.

278
00:11:01,830 --> 00:11:02,470
Alright.

279
00:11:02,622 --> 00:11:04,480
The worst that can happen is
to get a scolding.

280
00:11:04,488 --> 00:11:05,288
I'll go with Huixin.

281
00:11:06,110 --> 00:11:06,950
Huixin,

282
00:11:07,355 --> 00:11:08,577
see you this evening.

283
00:11:08,577 --> 00:11:09,710
Let's go back and tidy up.

284
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:10,110
Okay.

285
00:11:10,430 --> 00:11:11,590
Let's meet this evening.

286
00:11:11,590 --> 00:11:12,070
Wait.

287
00:11:12,260 --> 00:11:13,380
You'd better tidy up.

288
00:11:13,380 --> 00:11:15,190
Don't leave smelly socks
all over the place.

289
00:11:15,310 --> 00:11:16,500
How can that be?

290
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:18,680
The boys' dormitory is very clean.
Am I right, Zhou Ye?

291
00:11:18,688 --> 00:11:19,710
Clean? Is it clean?

292
00:11:19,830 --> 00:11:20,733
Of course it's clean.

293
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:21,777
We'll get going now.

294
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:22,070
